The following is a list of the Major League Baseball players with the highest career total of home runs by birth location. Statistics are current as of June 10 , 2008 . Players in boldface played at least one game in the major leagues in 2008 .
List of top home run hitters by birthplace

John Hattig is an active player for the Toronto Blue Jays and the first major leaguer from Guam ; he has yet to hit a home run. Bobby Fenwick was the only MLB player born in the Ryukyu Islands while they were occupied by the United States after World War II; he hit no home runs during his career.
